content:
Abu Layla said, "Salman went out and when his animal fodder fell
from the manger, he told his servant, 'If it were not that I fear retaliation,
I would make you hurt (i.e. by beating you)."

Ka'b ibn 'Ujra said, "Those who repeat the supplications which
follow the prayers will not be disappointed. They are: 'Glory be to Allah';
'Praise be to Allah'; and 'There is no god but Allah' a hundred times."
